init_text:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: With my commute, I listen to a lot of books, and I can’t imagine giving that up.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There are a lot of great things about audiobooks.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The obvious perk is that you can enjoy a book on the go, in the car, or while walking.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This is a great benefit, especially when you think of how much time we spend in the car or on public transportation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I feel like I am free to do other things while listening to an audiobook, like read something else, clean, or crochet.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I don’t need to focus on a story as much as I would with physical books.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I can daydream and do other activities.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It’s also nice not to have to sit still.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I feel like I can consume a book while running on the treadmill, or in other places where it’s hard to sit.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Finally, I listen to books when I am in bed at night.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It’s my time to unwind and give my brain some time off after the chaos of the day.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And, thanks to technology, I can keep the volume low while falling asleep.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Since they are digital, you don’t need books to be manufactured, stored, and transported.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There is also less book waste.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: Audiobooks are more ecofriendly. Since they are digital, you don’t need books to be manufactured, stored, and transported. There is also less book waste.  Regular books can mold, mildew, and spoil, but audiobooks are forever.
